+# Solution: Manage multiple properties using the same ComplexType in IUpdateAdapter.CreateEntry
+
+## Root Cause
+
+When `IUpdateAdapter.CreateEntry` (or `IStateManager.CreateEntry`) is called with a
+`IDictionary<string, object?>` of property values, `InternalEntityEntry` populates an
+internal value-buffer by iterating `entityType.GetFlattenedProperties()` and looking up each
+property using `property.Name`.
+
+With two entity properties of the same complex type (e.g. both `TaxInfoExtended` and
+`TaxInfoExtended2` are of type `TaxInfoExtended`), `GetFlattenedProperties()` yields two
+separate property instances named `"CodeExtended"` — one for each complex-property instance.
+Both property instances have **different** internal array indexes, but both resolve to the same
+dictionary key `"CodeExtended"`.  As a result:
+
+* Both slots in the value buffer receive the same value (the one stored under the
+  unambiguous key), so the second complex-property instance silently overwrites the first.
+* When no such key exists at all (as is the case for seed data, which stores whole complex
+  objects under the complex-property name) every leaf property falls back to its sentinel
+  value and the complex type's data is silently discarded.
+
+Exactly the same ambiguity exists in `ShadowValuesFactoryFactory`, which generates runtime
+expressions that look up shadow-property values by `property.Name`.
+
+## Change Description
+
+### New helper: `PropertyBaseExtensions.GetFlattenedPropertyKey`
+Added to `src/EFCore/Metadata/Internal/PropertyBaseExtensions.cs`.
+
+For a property directly on an entity type the key is unchanged (`property.Name`).
+For a property declared on a non-collection complex type the key is the dot-delimited chain of
+complex-property names followed by the leaf property name, e.g.:
+
+| Property | Key |
+|---|---|
+| `TaxInfo.TaxInfoId` | `"TaxInfoId"` |
+| `TaxInfo.TaxInfoExtended.CodeExtended` | `"TaxInfoExtended.CodeExtended"` |
+| `TaxInfo.TaxInfoExtended2.CodeExtended` | `"TaxInfoExtended2.CodeExtended"` |
+| `TaxInfo.TaxInfoExtended.Address.Street` | `"TaxInfoExtended.Address.Street"` |
+
+### `InternalEntityEntry` constructor
+`src/EFCore/ChangeTracking/Internal/InternalEntityEntry.cs` — replace `property.Name` with
+`property.GetFlattenedPropertyKey()` in the dictionary lookup used to populate the
+materialization value buffer.
+
+### `ShadowValuesFactoryFactory`
+`src/EFCore/ChangeTracking/Internal/ShadowValuesFactoryFactory.cs` — replace `property.Name`
+with `property.GetFlattenedPropertyKey()` in the generated expression that reads shadow
+property values from the dictionary.
+
+### `EntityType.GetSeedData`
+`src/EFCore/Metadata/Internal/EntityType.cs` — the non-anonymous-type path previously stored
+whole complex objects under the complex-property name (e.g. `"TaxInfoExtended"` →
+`TaxInfoExtended instance`).  These entries were never used by `InternalEntityEntry` (it
+looked for `"CodeExtended"`, not `"TaxInfoExtended"`), meaning seed data for complex types
+was silently dropped.
+
+The method now:
+1. No longer includes `GetComplexProperties()` in `propertiesList` (so no whole-object
+   entries are produced).
+2. After processing direct scalar and navigation properties, iterates
+   `GetFlattenedComplexProperties()` and for each non-collection complex property emits one
+   entry per declared scalar property, keyed with the full path key.  For each entry, it
+   navigates the CLR object via `GetMemberInfo` to extract the actual value.
+
+### `IUpdateAdapter.CreateEntry` documentation
+`src/EFCore/Update/IUpdateAdapter.cs` — updated XML doc for the `values` parameter to explain
+the path-based key convention and why it is required for disambiguation.
+
+## Files Edited
+
+* `src/EFCore/Metadata/Internal/PropertyBaseExtensions.cs`
+* `src/EFCore/ChangeTracking/Internal/InternalEntityEntry.cs`
+* `src/EFCore/ChangeTracking/Internal/ShadowValuesFactoryFactory.cs`
+* `src/EFCore/Metadata/Internal/EntityType.cs`
+* `src/EFCore/Update/IUpdateAdapter.cs`
+
+## Precedent Usage
+
+### Query 1
+`"complex type property path disambiguation flattened properties same name"`
+
+Score 0.459 — PR #37919 (Cosmos complex property name configuration).  Not directly
+applicable; describes a different extension point.  **Ignored, not useful.**
+
+### Query 2
+`"IUpdateAdapter CreateEntry dictionary values complex type multiple properties"`
+
+Below threshold (0.406) — PR #37762 (nullable complex property `InvalidCastException`).
+This was a different bug in `ArrayPropertyValues`, not the dictionary-key lookup.
+**Ignored, not useful.**
+
+### Query 3
+`"InternalEntityEntry constructor values dictionary complex property GetComplexPropertyChain"`
+
+Below threshold (0.447) — same PR #37762 again.  **Ignored, not useful.**
